
Overview of verb afford

The verb afford has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (24) afford -- (be able to spare or give up; "I can't afford to spend two hours with this person")
2. (13) yield, give, afford -- (be the cause or source of; "He gave me a lot of trouble"; "Our meeting afforded much interesting information")
3. afford -- (have the financial means to do something or buy something; "We can't afford to send our children to college"; "Can you afford this car?")
4. afford, open, give -- (afford access to; "the door opens to the patio"; "The French doors give onto a terrace")
